snippet: The Orioles rapped seven hits against Masahiro Tanaka, and a few other hard-hit outs. They also took some wild swings on balls in the dirt, underscoring the quality of the Japanese import’s repertory.
abstract: Tyler Kepner On Baseball column; Baltimore Orioles collected seven hits against New York Yankees' newest Japanese pitching sensation Masahiro Tanaka, and took some wild swings on balls in the dirt, underscoring the quality of Tanaka's repertory.
lead_paragraph: The Orioles rapped seven hits against Masahiro Tanaka, and a few other hard-hit outs. They also took some wild swings on balls in the dirt, underscoring the quality of the Japanese import’s repertory.

headline.main: Orioles Are Impressed, if Not Overly So, by Tanaka
headline.print_headline: Orioles Are Impressed, if Not Overly So, by a New Yankee
